lzh_formatted:
  title: 寶位
  author: 金坵
  language: lzh
  text: 恪守靑丘。厚沐漸東之化。遙瞻紫極。益殫拱北之虔。嘉與兆民。切祈遐筭。
korean:
  title: 새로 보위
  author: 김구
  language: kor
  text: 삼가 청구(靑丘)를 지키면서 두터이 동점(東漸)의 황화(皇化)에 목욕(沐浴)하옵니다. 멀리 자신(紫宸)을 바라보며 더욱 충성의 마음을 다하면서 조민(兆民)과 기쁨을 함께하여 만세(萬歲)의 성수(聖壽)를 간절히 비옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0050&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: The Precious Throne
  author: Kim Gu
  language: eng
  text: |-
    With reverence I guard the Eastern Land,
    Bathed in the grace that flows from the imperial court.
    Gazing far toward the Purple Palace of Heaven,
    I dedicate myself ever more to loyal devotion.
    Joining my heart with all the people,
    I humbly pray for the sovereign's ten thousand years.
  footnotes:
    - The 'Eastern Land' (靑丘, Cheonggu) is a classical reference to Korea.
    - The 'Purple Palace of Heaven' (紫宸, Jajin) traditionally refers to the throne or the seat of imperial authority.
    - The prayer for 'ten thousand years' (萬歲, manse) is a traditional expression wishing longevity and prosperity to the ruler.
